org.modelio.api.modelio.diagram

Interface IDiagramService


  • public interface IDiagramService
    This interface gives an entry point to manipulate the Modelio diagrams.
    It also manages diagram customization and diagram styles.

                           java.lang.String baseStyleName,
                           java.io.File styleData)
        Register a new named style along with its 'data' file.
        Parameters:
        styleName - then name of the style to register.
        baseStyleName - the cascaded style.
        styleData - the list of all properties defined in the style.
        Returns:
        then newly created IStyleHandle or null if the style could not be created. When the style already exists it is simply returned.

      • getDiagramTemplate

        IModelViewTemplate<AbstractDiagram> getDiagramTemplate(java.lang.String modelViewTemplateId)
        Get a Diagram Creator from its id. Supported values are:
        Creator identifier Description
        "ClassArchitectureDiagramTemplate" A Class Architecture diagram shows how a class is made, what it consists of, what it is in terms of inheritance and its place in the project.

        For a class, it includes:

        • The class itself in the center.
        • Its public attributes.
        • The parent classes/interfaces if any.
        • The child classes/interfaces if any.
        • The classes it is having an association to.
        • The classes having any kind of association towards it.
        "ClassStructureDiagramTemplate" A Class Structure diagram shows how a class is made, what it consists of, what it is in terms of inheritance.

        For a class, it includes:

        • The class itself in the center.
        • Its public attributes.
        • The parent classes/interfaces if any.
        • The classes it is having an association to.
        • The classes having a composition or aggregation towards it.
        "CompositionNavigationDiagramTemplate" A Composition diagram shows owned elements of a ModelTree.

        For a ModelTree, it includes:

        • The owned ModelTrees layouted on a grid.
        "DependencyDiagramTemplate" A Dependency diagram shows incoming and outgoing dependencies of a NameSpace.

        For a NameSpace, it includes:

        • The NameSpace itself in a central position.
        • All elements having a dependency towards the NameSpace on the left.
        • All elements having the NameSpace depends on on the right.
        "InheritanceDiagramTemplate" A Class Inheritance diagram shows where a Classifier is in its inheritance graph.

        For a Classifier, it includes:

        • The Classifier itself in the center.
        • The parent classes/interfaces if any.
        • The parent sub-classes if any.
        "PackageContentStructureDiagramTemplate" A SubPackage Structure diagram shows the internal structure of a package, and the links between them.

        For a package, it includes:

        • Its sub-classes/interfaces.
        • The associations and inheritance relationships between them.
        "SubPackageStructureDiagramTemplate" A SubPackage Structure diagram shows the internal structure of a Package or Component in terms of packages, and the dependencies between them.

        It includes:

        • Its sub-packages.
        • The blue links (impact links) between those sub-packages.
        "UseCaseFocusDiagramTemplate" A 'Use Case close up' diagram shows for a UseCase:
        • The use case itself.
        • The actors associated to the use case
        • The associations between actors and usecase
        Parameters:
        modelViewTemplateId - identifier of the diagram template.
        Returns:
        a new Diagram Creator. Might be null if the id is not found.
        Since:
        4.1
